ElementDescription: The NDAR Global Unique Identifier (GUID) for research subject
Subject ID how it's defined in lab/project
Age in months at the time of the interview/test/sampling/imaging.
Notes: Age is rounded to chronological month. If the research participant is 15-days-old at time of interview, the appropriate value would be 0 months. If the participant is 16-days-old, the value would be 1 month.

ElementDescription: Date on which the interview/genetic test/sampling/imaging/biospecimen was completed. MM/DD/YYYY
Sex of subject at birth
Notes: M = Male; F = Female; O=Other; NR = Not reported

ElementDescription: Subject's gender OTHER describe
BS-SNI Sum Score
How many close friends do you have, people that you feel at ease with, can talk to about private matters?
Notes: 0 = None; 1 = 1 or 2; 2 = 3 to 5; 3 = 6 to 9; 4 = 10 or more

ElementDescription: How many of these close friends do you see at least once a month?
Notes: 0 = None; 1 = 1 or 2; 2 = 3 to 5; 3 = 6 to 9; 4 = 10 or more

ElementDescription: How many relatives do you have, people, that you feel at ease with, can talk to about private matters?
Notes: 0 = None; 1 = 1 or 2; 2 = 3 to 5; 3 = 6 to 9; 4 = 10 or more

ElementDescription: How many of these relatives do you see at least once a month?
Notes: 0 = None; 1 = 1 or 2; 2 = 3 to 5; 3 = 6 to 9; 4 = 10 or more

ElementDescription: Do you participate in any groups such as a senior center, social or work group, religious-connected group, self-help group, or charity, public service, or community group?
About how often do you go to religious meetings or services?
Notes: 0 = Never or almost never; 1 = Once or twice a year; 2 = Every few months; 3 = Once or twice a month; 4 = Once a week; 5 = More than once a week

ElementDescription: How many people are available to you whom you can count on to listen to you when you need to talk?
Notes: 0 = None; 1 = 1 or 2; 2 = 3 to 5; 3 = 6 to 9; 4 = 10 or more

Notes: 0 = None; 1 = 1 or 2; 2 = 3 to 5; 3 = 6 to 9; 4 = 10 or more

Notes: 0 = None; 1 = 1 or 2; 2 = 3 to 5; 3 = 6 to 9; 4 = 10 or more

ElementDescription: How many people can you count on to provide you with emotional support (talking over problems or helping you make a difficult decision)?
Notes: 0 = None; 1 = 1 or 2; 2 = 3 to 5; 3 = 6 to 9; 4 = 10 or more

ElementDescription: Do you have as much contact as you would like with someone you feel close to, someone in whom you can trust and confide?
Notes: 0 = None; 1 = 1 or 2; 2 = 3 to 5; 3 = 6 to 9; 4 = 10 or more

ElementDescription: How many people can you count on to listen to you when you need to talk?
Notes: 0 = None; 1 = 1 or 2; 2 = 3 to 5; 3 = 6 to 9; 4 = 10 or more

ElementDescription: How many people show you love and affection?
Notes: 0 = None; 1 = 1 or 2; 2 = 3 to 5; 3 = 6 to 9; 4 = 10 or more

ElementDescription: Timepoint/visit label
